<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-035-213 </DOCNO><DOCID>11 441 785</DOCID><JOURNAL>InfoWorld  Oct 14 1991 v13 n41 p100(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>TI's TravelMate WinSX serves up Windows to go. (Texas InstrumentsTravelMate 3000 WinSX notebook computer) (evaluation)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Needleman, Raphael.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Texas Instruments Inc's $3,499 TravelMate 300 WinSX notebookcomputer uses a 20-MHz 80386SX microprocessor and is designedespecially for running the Microsoft Windows interface.andP;  Windows3.0 is pre-installed on the 60Mbyte hard disk, and 4Mbytes of RAMis standard.andP;  TI provides a side-mounted 'TravelPoint' trackballas well as DOS 5.0.andP;  The screen is an easy-to-read VGA LCD thatcan show 32 levels of gray, and the TravelPoint is easy to use.andO;Its roller ball moves smoothly, and there is a convenientclick-lock button for dragging items.andP;  The machine has manypower-saving features; the screen, hard disk and CPU can all beset to reduce power consumption or power off after user-definedperiods of inactivity.andP;  It is one of the few notebooks thatupdates the Windows clock when in 'sleep' mode.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Texas Instruments Inc. (Products).andO;Ticker:    TXN.andO;Product:   Texas Instruments TravelMate 3000 WinSX (Portable computer)(evaluation).andO;Topic:     Laptop computersEvaluationNotebook Computers.andO;Feature:   illustrationphotograph.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>